review_blob: What an incredibly Lager.  I wasnt expecting this at all.  It has an out-of-this-world hop aroma almost akin to a Pale Ale.  I love it.  It is creamy and has a wonderful body, not too light or crisp as some Lagers get.  Its pale in color, like a bright straw yellow with white head.  Super easy drinking but very flavorful at the same time.  Might be my new favorite.

Wow, this cider left me with a huge smile on my face.  The higher alcohol is not apparent at all.  It has a great cloudy color that reminds me of an unfiltered wheat beer.  Has a nice head like beer too.  Then the taste is a softly sweet apple with that creamy vanilla undertone that sets it apart from any other cider Ive had.  I tried this one cold but Ive heard it is great warmed up with a cinnamon stick and some orange zest.  Yum.
beer_name: J.K.s Cuve Winterruption Farmhouse Hard Cider

review_blob: Skrumpy has a tart apple smell up front.   Then the flavor brings that sweet apple pie, creamy goodness.  This cider pours unfiltered and hazy and is very drinkable even with its sugar.  A sampled this both hot and cold and loved them both
beer_name: J.K.s Scrumpy Orchard Gate Gold Hard Cider

review_blob: This might be the most full-flavored and drinkable amber Ive had in a while.
This might be the perfect pairing for a cigar.  It is slightly smoky and has great bourbon barrel vanilla flavors.  Just enough sweetness too.
The sublte note of green apple along with all of the fig, caramel, vanilla, etc. make this beer fantastic.  It also has a wonderful texture: creamy and delicious.
beer_name: Gouden Carolus Cuvee Van De Keizer Blauw/Blue
